<dl id="n12153l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12153l">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12153l"> 153(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> give you 2 months to / prove him a heretic</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">As to C&aelig;lestius &hellip; the pope charged the Africans either to revise their former sentence or to convict him of heresy in his own (the pope&apos;s) presence within two months. <small> <a name="CEPEL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CEPEL"><cite title="source">&ldquo;Pelagius&rdquo;</cite></a> <cite a>Catholic Encyclopaedia</cite></a> (1911) 606b</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12159e" href="c12all.htm#c12159e">VI.C.12:159(e)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
